tlsdate (0.0.7-1.3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Non-maintainer upload in coordination with the maintainer.
  * Rename debian/tlsdate.init to debian/tlsdated.init (to match the
    systemd service file) and modify it's content to match. (Closes: #758677)
  * Thus also rename debian/tlsdate.default to debian/tlsdated.default.
  * Add preinst, postinst and postrm maintainer script to handle this
    conffile renaming properly.
  * Ship copy debian/tlsdated.service with one single change: /usr/sbin as
    the path. (This is temporarily, until the fixed service file has become
    part of the next upstream release.)
  * Add lintian override for possible-gpl-code-linked-with-openssl warning as
    only the AppArmor profile is GPL licensed.
  * Add dh-autoreconf and dh-systemd to build-depends.

 -- Holger Levsen <holger@debian.org>  Fri, 22 Aug 2014 19:36:20 -0700

tlsdate (0.0.7-1.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Non-maintainer upload.
  * Remove build-depends on hardening-wrapper and instead raise dependency on
    debhelper 9 and use that and dpkg-buildflags to achieve the same.
  * Use dh-autoreconf (Closes: #744526)
  * Make lintian and everybody happy:
    - don't install LICENSE file as the information is contained in
      debian/copyright already.
    - install upstream CHANGELOG as changelog as mandated by Debian Policy.

 -- Holger Levsen <holger@debian.org>  Tue, 19 Aug 2014 17:32:08 -0400

